EXHIBIT A

✅ 1. SAFE Decision Matrix
For Investment Club LLC Nominee Structure
 (Attach as an Exhibit to the Nominee Rider or Operating Agreement)

SAFE DECISION MATRIX
Exhibit ___ to Nominee Rider
This Decision Matrix defines how decisions relating to the SAFE (the “SAFE”) shall be made by:
Nominee (Master Series Investment Club LLC)


Nominee Delegate (Individual)


Beneficial Owners (Individual Series LLC)


The Company may rely on decisions communicated by the Nominee Delegate unless replaced or revoked in writing.

A. Administration & Notices (Delegate Authority)
Actions the Nominee Delegate may take alone, without a member vote, provided the Delegate acts in good faith and in the best interest of the Beneficial Owners:
Action
Authority
Notes
Receiving all communications, notices, updates from the Company
Nominee Delegate
Delegate must distribute material notices to Beneficial Owners.
Executing ministerial documents (acknowledgments, receipt confirmations, informational forms)
Nominee Delegate
Must not alter economic or ownership rights.
Updating contact information or administrative records
Nominee Delegate
Purely clerical.
Converting the SAFE into issued shares if conversion is automatic and non-discretionary
Nominee Delegate
Applies only to standard, automatic conversion events triggered by the SAFE.
Accepting updated disclosure packets from the Company
Nominee Delegate
Routine items only.


B. Actions Requiring Majority Vote of Beneficial Owners (Default: Simple Majority)
These actions must be approved by Beneficial Owners holding a majority of the membership interests of the Nominee, unless the Nominee’s operating agreement sets a higher threshold.
Action
Required Approval
Notes
Providing a waiver under the SAFE
Majority Vote
Unless required urgently and no harm results, Delegate must seek vote.
Voting on “Holder Approval” matters required by Company
Majority Vote
e.g., amendments to financing documents.
Electing optional conversion (if applicable)
Majority Vote
Rare, but exists in some SAFE variants.
Approving amendments to the SAFE that materially affect rights
Majority Vote
Delegate cannot act alone.
Appointing a new Nominee Delegate
Majority Vote
Provided for in Rider.
Removing a Nominee Delegate
Majority Vote
Unless automatic removal triggered by incapacity or resignation.


C. Actions Requiring Supermajority Vote (Recommended: 2/3 or ≥ 66%)
These are major changes affecting ownership, economics, or long-term outcomes.
Action
Required Approval
Notes
Selling or transferring the SAFE
Supermajority (66%+)
Only if allowed by Company or law.
Approving side letters that alter economics
Supermajority
Ensures fairness to all members.
Merging the Club’s interest into another SPV or Nominee
Supermajority
Often used before priced rounds.
Approving liquidation or dissolution of the Nominee LLC prior to conversion
Supermajority
Ensures stable ownership before conversion.


D. Actions Requiring Unanimous Consent
These actions affect all members equally and therefore require 100% consent:
Action
Required Approval
Notes
Altering pro-rata allocations of economic rights among members
Unanimous
Protects all members’ equity.
Assigning the SAFE to an entity that changes member beneficial interests
Unanimous
Protects minority holders.
Changing the legal structure that determines beneficial ownership (e.g., changing vesting terms)
Unanimous
Ensures no one is involuntarily diluted.


E. Emergency Decision Authority
If the Company requires a response within a time period too short for the Delegate to reasonably obtain a member vote:
The Nominee Delegate may act in good-faith administrative discretion
 if and only if failing to act would materially harm the Beneficial Owners.


Delegate must later provide written notice to Beneficial Owners describing the action taken.



