 Phone: ___________________________________
as the Nominee Delegate, authorized to act on behalf of the Nominee in connection with the SAFE and any resulting securities, subject to the terms of:
the Nominee Rider (SAFE Edition), and


the Nominee’s Operating Agreement.



2. Scope of Authority
The Nominee Delegate is granted a limited, revocable power of attorney to:
Receive notices and communications from the Company.


Execute administrative documents relating to the SAFE.


Cast votes, provide consents, and deliver Holder Approvals as authorized by the Beneficial Owners under the Decision Matrix.


Perform ministerial actions required to maintain or administer the Nominee’s rights.


The Nominee Delegate shall not:
assign or sell the SAFE,


amend terms affecting economic rights,


or take discretionary actions outside the bounds of the Decision Matrix
 unless properly authorized by the Beneficial Owners.



3. Company Reliance
The Company may:
rely conclusively on communications from the Nominee Delegate,


treat all such communications as valid instructions from the Nominee,


until the Company receives a replacement certificate or written revocation.



4. Replacement or Removal
The Beneficial Owners may:
remove the Nominee Delegate, and


appoint a successor Nominee Delegate


at any time via majority vote (or per the Nominee’s Operating Agreement).
A replacement becomes effective once the Company receives a written updated Appointment Certificate.

